==English==
===Transitive verb===
'''to [[round]] [[up]]''' ('''rounds up''', '''rounding up''', '''rounded up''')

#{{idiom}} To [[collect]] or [[gather]] (something) [[together]].
#:'''''Round up''' the usual suspects.''
#{{arithmetic}} To [[round]] (a number) to the smallest [[integer]] that is not less than it, or to some other greater value, especially a whole number of hundreds, thousands, etc.
#:''The total is $24,995 &mdash; let's '''round up''' to $25,000.''

